thomas c langdon 84 a retired editor of 
the pittsburgh press died friday of congestive heart failure and 
pneumonia 
langdon worked for newspapers in washington dc mississippi 
and west virginia before becoming city editor of the mckeesport 
pa journal in 1925 he later was managing editor of the journal 
before joining the press in 1926 
he left the press after six months to become managing editor of 
the altoona tribune but he rejoined the press in 1929 and stayed 
for 40 years 
langdon worked on the newspapers telegraph city copy and 
features desks and was assistant news editor for 16 years 
