pope john paul ii proclaimed an easter 
sunday message of hope tinged with sadness recalling those 
persecuted for their faith the breakup of families and sectarian 
strife 
about 100000 pilgrims tourists and romans jammed into saint 
peters square to hear the pope say midmorning easter mass on the 
steps of christianitys largest basilica 
he later moved to the balcony to deliver his speech and easter 
greetings in 55 languages by then the crowd had nearly doubled 
spilling over into narrow and cobblestone streets surrounding 
vatican city 
keeping with easter tradition the pope who is head of the 
roman catholic church and titular bishop of rome delivered his 
easter message urbi et orbi latin meaning to the city and 
the world 
on easter christians celebrate their belief in the resurrection 
of christ from his tomb following his death on the cross on good 
friday 
calling easter the new passover in reference to the night 
the jews were miraculously saved in egypt the pope said god 
continues to pass through the world through the resurrection of 
his son the son of man 
god passes and frees from the fear that oppresses so many of 
our brothers and sisters john paul said 
he passes where there do not exist conditions worthy of a 
truly human life the pope added he cited poor housing broken 
marriages prostitution and countries where people cannot freely 
worship 
he did not name any country 
god passes where the longedfor peace is not yet to be 
seen the pope said singling out sectarian strife in lebanon 
god still passes and sets free the whole of creation in 
his blood all is reconciled man with god with himself with 
nature the pope said at this point the responsibility of man 
gains new strength and awareness 
this is the truth which easter proclaims to todays world 
which is so many ways seems to be rushing headlong towards 
selfdestruction and death the pope said 
