<DOCNO> AP890326-0010 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
in a new play about menachem begin the 
enigmatic former israeli leader fantasizes about bombing germany to 
retaliate for the holocaust and imagines being mobbed by admirers 
after ending his selfimposed seclusion 
the oneman play was written for the israel festival in may but 
was rejected by festival officials who feared such freewheeling 
treatment of the 75yearold begin was too controversial 
the rejection highlights the ambivalence and strong emotions 
begin still generates among israelis nearly six years after he 
unexpectedly resigned as prime minister and shut himself in his 
twostory apartment at the edge of the jerusalem pine forest 
to the nationalists begin is a sacred man a symbol of 
everything that is pure and good to those on the left he stands 
for everything they despise said ehud sprinzak a hebrew 
university professor and expert on rightwing israeli politics 
begin became prime minister in 1977 the first from the 
rightwing likud bloc to hold the post two years later he signed 
the historic peace treaty with egypt sharing the nobel peace prize 
with president anwar sadat of egypt he resigned in 1983 at the 
height of the war in lebanon 
today begins life is shrouded in mystery frustrating 
biographers and heightening curiosity among israelis 
he ventures outside his apartment for a public appearance only 
once a year to attend a memorial service for his wife aliza who 
died in 1982 
begin breaks his silence rarely usually to comment briefly on 
the radio about history he refuses to discuss his resignation 
commonly attributed to depression over the death of his wife and 
the lebanon war in which more than 600 israelis died 
on sunday begin commented on the 10th anniversary of the 
israelegypt peace accord taking the unusual step of speaking 
about current politics and criticizing the new american dialogue 
with the plo as a negative harmful phenomenon 
he spends his days reading books mostly biographies and 
history said longtime begin aide yehiel kadishai he said begin 
keeps up with news programs reads israeli and foreign newspapers 
and answers several dozen letters a week 
once an avid moviegoer he now watches videos in the evenings 
he likes westerns said kadishai adding that the former prime 
minister also used to watch the american soap opera dallas 
american oil magnate armand hammer offered to donate 750000 to 
begins favorite charity if the former prime minister wrote his 
autobiography but begin has declined kadishai said 
his family aides and friends refuse to talk about begin in what 
israeli journalists have described as a wall of silence 
justice minister dan meridor a longtime friend visits begin 
every friday to talk politics when asked for details about the 
talks meridor balked ive never spoken about my conversations 
with begin 
israeli journalist amnon dankner tried to skirt these obstacles 
and probe the former prime ministers psyche in his oneman play 
titled simply begin 
in one scene begin imagines ending his seclusion people will 
see me and will be amazed he says dreaming of a crowd cheering 
and shouting long live begin 
but then he stops himself and asks what would be the point of 
all those years all the silence the selfimprisonment 
in another scene begin fantasizes about ordering a strike 
against germany in retaliation for the nazi holocaust in which 6 
million jews including begins parents and brother were killed 
on that day bodies would pile up at the entrances of towns 
and squares like they were piled up at the entrances of the 
camps says the begin character 
dankner said he and many other israelis share these revenge 
fantasies adding that begins ability to articulate such emotions 
was at the root of his popularity 
in every israeli there is a little begin he said he 
expressed our fears our nightmares our delusions of grandeur 
even today the mention of begin sparks strong reactions 
during an election rally last fall likud followers listened 
politely to speeches by party leaders but at the mention of 
begins name worked themselves into a frenzy clapping and shouting 
the name of the former leader for several minutes 
but anger toward begin has remained just as strong 
while begin celebrated his birthday last summer a crowd 
gathered outside his apartment including a jerusalem woman whose 
son was killed in the june 1982 lebanon invasion 
this man caused dozens of young men not to reach even their 
20th birthdays said the woman raya harnik in the middle of 
the war he just said he couldnt go on any longer the bereaved 
parents never had such a privilege 
</TEXT>
