voters in phoenix and its suburbs decide tuesday 
whether to add a halfpenny to their sales tax to finance an 84 
billion highway and transit program including a controversial 
103mile elevated railway 
the metropolitan area of 2 million people is the nations 
largest without an integrated freeway system a vast grid of 
northsouth eastwest streets is stamped across the desert 
relieved only by two interstate highways and a piece of state 
freeway 
maricopa county residents are saddled with some of the highest 
autoinsurance rates in the nation partly because of intersection 
collisions 
the population of this valley is going to double in the 
future whether we like it or not says herb drinkwater mayor of 
the wealthy suburb of scottsdale ive been here 43 years and i 
dont always like it but we have to deal with it and theres no 
way that there can be enough roads built to handle the traffic 
weve got to get out of our cars and get them off the road 
